Capitis deminutio media occurred also when a Roman citizen became civis of another town, e. g. a civitas peregrina or a Latin colony, between which and Rome there was not a complete community of civil rights, Cic. pro Balbo 11.12, pro Caec. 33. 34, de Orat. 1. 40.
